      "rawResponseJson": "{\n  \"thought\": \"I found that Etsy search results do expose reliable /listing/ hrefs, including a strong candidate '2025 Family Christmas Ornament, Personalized Ornament with Names...' with a direct listing URL. The previous click failed because the selector likely hit a non-navigating element. Next I should patch final_script.py to extract the first suitable Etsy /listing/ URL from anchors via evaluate_all, navigate directly to it, wait, and then extract h1 and price. After that I need to rerun run_1, inspect artifacts, and only then try self_reflection if the Etsy summary is populated.\",\n  \"bash_command\": \"cd RELEASE_WORKSPACE && python - <<'PY'\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\np = Path('final_script.py')\\ntext = p.read_text()\\nstart = text.index(\\\"        await page.screenshot(path=str(SCREENSHOTS / 'final_execution_1_etsy_search_results.png'))\\\")\\nend = text.index(\\\"        # Amazon direct product page in its own tab\\\")\\nreplacement = \\\"\\\"\\\"        await page.screenshot(path=str(SCREENSHOTS / 'final_execution_1_etsy_search_results.png'))\\\\n        try:\\\\n            raw_body = await page.locator('body').inner_text(timeout=5000)\\\\n        except Exception:\\\\n            raw_body = await page.content()\\\\n        body_text = re.sub(r'\\\\\\\\s+', ' ', raw_body)[:2500]\\\\n        title = await page.title()\\\\n        log(f'step 4 action: Etsy page state after search attempt at {page.url} with title {title} and body snippet: {body_text}')\\\\n        try:\\\\n            etsy_links = await page.locator('a').evaluate_all(\\\\\\\"els => els.map(a => ({text:(a.innerText||a.getAttribute('aria-label')||'').replace(/\\\\\\\\s+/g,' ').trim(), href:a.href||''})).filter(x => x.href.includes('/listing/') && /family|personalized|name|ornament/i.test(x.text)).slice(0,20)\\\\\\\")\\\\n            chosen = None\\\\n            for item in etsy_links:\\\\n                if 'family' in item['text'].lower() and ('name' in item['text'].lower() or 'names' in item['text'].lower() or '2025' in item['text'].lower()):\\\\n                    chosen = item\\\\n                    break\\\\n            if not chosen and etsy_links:\\\\n                chosen = etsy_links[0]\\\\n            if not chosen:\\\\n                raise RuntimeError('No Etsy listing href found')\\\\n            await page.goto(chosen['href'], wait_until='domcontentloaded', timeout=60000)\\\\n            await page.wait_for_timeout(8000)\\\\n            summary['etsy_name'] = (await page.locator('h1').first.inner_text(timeout=10000)).strip()\\\\n            price_loc = page.locator('[data-selector=\\\\\\\"price-only\\\\\\\"]').first\\\\n            if await price_loc.count() == 0:\\\\n                price_loc = page.locator('p.wt-text-title-larger').first\\\\n            summary['etsy_price'] = (await price_loc.inner_text(timeout=8000)).strip()\\\\n            log(f'step 5 action: opened Etsy listing page {page.url} from candidate {chosen[\\\"text\\\"]} and extracted title {summary[\\\"etsy_name\\\"]} with price {summary[\\\"etsy_price\\\"]}')\\\\n            await page.screenshot(path=str(SCREENSHOTS / 'final_execution_2_etsy_listing.png'))\\\\n        except Exception as e:\\\\n            log(f'step 5 action: Etsy listing open/extraction failed with {type(e).__name__}; keeping search-results evidence only')\\\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\ntext = text[:start] + replacement + text[end:]\\np.write_text(text)\\nPY\\npython final_script.py && echo '---LOG---' && cat final_runs/run_1/final_script_log.txt && echo '---SCREENSHOTS---' && ls -R final_runs/run_1/screenshots\",\n  \"done\": false,\n  \"final_response\": \"\"\n}",
